text: Jack County is a county in the U.S. state of Texas. In 2020, 8,472 people lived there. The county seat is Jacksboro. == History == The county was founded in 1857. == Geography == The county has a total area of 920 square miles. == Places == === Cities === * Bryson * Jacksboro (county seat) == References == Category:Texas counties
title: Jack County, Texas
